project.name: node-gdal
project.description: Node.js bindings for GDAL (Geospatial Data Abstraction Library)

gdal.Envelope.name: gdal.Envelope
gdal.Envelope.description:
A 2D bounding box. For 3D envelopes, see {{#crossLink "gdal.Envelope3D"}}gdal.Envelope3D{{/crossLink}}.

(Pure-javascript implementation of [OGREnvelope](http://www.gdal.org/classOGREnvelope.html))

gdal.Envelope3D.name: gdal.Envelope3D
gdal.Envelope3D.description:
A 3D bounding box. For 2D envelopes, see {{#crossLink "gdal.Envelope"}}gdal.Envelope{{/crossLink}}.

(Pure-javascript implementation of [OGREnvelope3D](http://www.gdal.org/classOGREnvelope3D.html))

gdal.GeometryCollectionChildren.name: gdal.GeometryCollectionChildren
gdal.GeometryCollectionChildren.description: A collection of Geometries, used by {{#crossLink "gdal.GeometryCollection"}}gdal.GeometryCollection{{/crossLink}}.

gdal.PolygonRings.name: gdal.PolygonRings
gdal.PolygonRings.description: A collection of polygon rings, used by {{#crossLink "gdal.Polygon"}}gdal.Polygon{{/crossLink}}.

gdal.name: gdal
gdal.description:
This [node-gdal](https://github.com/naturalatlas/node-gdal) GDAL binding for
Node.js provides a feature-complete way of reading, writing, and manipulating
geospatial data (raster and vector).

gdal.Dataset.name: gdal.Dataset
gdal.Dataset.description: A set of associated raster bands, usually from one file.

gdal.Driver.name: gdal.Driver
gdal.Driver.description:
Format specific driver.

An instance of this class is created for each supported format, and
manages information about the format.

This roughly corresponds to a file format, though some drivers may
be gateways to many formats through a secondary multi-library.

gdal.Feature.name: gdal.Feature
gdal.Feature.description: A simple feature, including geometry and attributes.

gdal.FeatureDefn.name: gdal.FeatureDefn
gdal.FeatureDefn.description: Definition of a feature class or feature layer.

gdal.Geometry.name: gdal.Geometry
gdal.Geometry.description: Abstract base class for all geometry classes.

gdal.GeometryCollection.name: gdal.GeometryCollection
gdal.GeometryCollection.description: A collection of 1 or more geometry objects.

gdal.LinearRing.name: gdal.LinearRing
gdal.LinearRing.description: Concrete representation of a closed ring.

gdal.LineString.name: gdal.LineString
gdal.LineString.description: Concrete representation of a multi-vertex line.

classitems.description:
Create vector contours from raster DEM.

This algorithm will generate contour vectors for the input raster band on the
requested set of contour levels. The vector contours are written to the passed
in vector layer. Also, a NODATA value may be specified to identify pixels
that should not be considered in contour line generation.
classitems.name: contourGenerate

classitems.description: Removes small raster polygons.
classitems.name: sieveFilter

props.name: dst
props.description: Output raster band. It may be the same as src band to update the source in place.

props.name: mask
props.description: All pixels in the mask band with a value other than zero will be considered suitable for inclusion in polygons.

props.name: threshold
props.description: Raster polygons with sizes smaller than this will be merged into their largest neighbour.

props.name: connectedness
props.description: Either 4 indicating that diagonal pixels are not considered directly adjacent for polygon membership purposes or 8 indicating they are.

classitems.description: Compute checksum for image region.
classitems.name: checksumImage

classitems.description:
Creates vector polygons for all connected regions of pixels in the raster
sharing a common pixel value. Each polygon is created with an attribute
indicating the pixel value of that polygon. A raster mask may also be
provided to determine which pixels are eligible for processing.
classitems.name: polygonize

props.name: pixValField
props.description: The attribute field index indicating the feature attribute into which the pixel value of the polygon should be written.

props.name: connectedness
props.description: Either 4 indicating that diagonal pixels are not considered directly adjacent for polygon membership purposes or 8 indicating they are.

props.name: useFloats
props.description: Use floating point buffers instead of int buffers.

classitems.description:
Apply arbitrary coordinate transformation to the geometry.

This method will transform the coordinates of a geometry from their current
spatial reference system to a new target spatial reference system. Normally
this means reprojecting the vectors, but it could include datum shifts,
and changes of units.

Note that this method does not require that the geometry already have a
spatial reference system. It will be assumed that they can be treated as
having the source spatial reference system of the {{#crossLink "gdal.CoordinateTransformation"}}CoordinateTransformation{{/crossLink}}
object, and the actual SRS of the geometry will be ignored.
classitems.name: transform
